snippet.textDisplay:
I've been a fan of Colour Blind since their 1997 eponymous album. And i've followed Ram Sampath's meandering career.
I like most of his work and i think he's an amazing composer, musician and singer, but this one brought some mixed feelings. 

The English bits seem so out of place and force-fitted because they're sung in a hasty tempo.
Aditi Singh Sharma does have a powerful and lovely voice, but every melody needs to be sung at its natural tempo for its poignancy to come through. 
I hope Ram Sampath realises this and mends it to perfection. 

SUGGESTION: Since there are interludes between the English and the Bangla bits, it's possible to blend two different tempos. So, the English part can be sung in its original tempo, which is perfect. Not only will it lend the song great cadence and movement, it will also take it from being [just] a lovely piece to a GREAT one.

The Bangla part is beautiful, but it's from a traditional folk song, and not entirely Ram Sampath's composition. However, i can appreciate his arrangement work.
